I paid no attention.

2067
01:52:34,650 --> 01:52:38,115
“He was a right elegant
Dominicker,” he continued.

2068
01:52:38,115 --> 01:52:41,923
I felt a little riled about the snapping-
turtle, and showed no interest in what he

2069
01:52:41,923 --> 01:52:45,065
was saying, but continued my
functions among the hens.

2070
01:52:45,065 --> 01:52:49,481
This unusual silence of mine seemed to
elicit unusual speech from him.

2071
01:52:49,481 --> 01:52:53,201
“Yu’ see, that rooster he’d always lived
round hyeh when the Judge was a

2072
01:52:53,201 --> 01:52:57,406
bachelor, and he never seen no ladies or
any persons wearing female gyarments.

2073
01:52:57,406 --> -1:59:59,000
You ain’t got rheumatism, seh?

2074
-1:59:59,000 --> 00:00:02,000
”

2075
01:53:00,030 --> 01:53:00,624
“Me?

2076
01:53:00,624 --> 01:53:01,335
No.”

2077
01:53:01,335 --> 01:53:05,125
“I reckoned maybe them little odd divers
yu’ got damp goin’ afteh⁠—”

2078
01:53:05,125 --> 01:53:06,486
He paused.

2079
01:53:06,486 --> 01:53:09,009
“Oh, no, not in the least, thank you.”

2080
01:53:09,009 --> 01:53:12,526
“Yu’ seemed sort o’ grave this mawnin’,
and I’m cert’nly glad

2081
01:53:12,526 --> 01:53:14,108
it ain’t them divers.”

2082
01:53:14,108 --> 01:53:16,146
“Well, the rooster?”

2083
01:53:16,146 --> 01:53:17,817
I inquired finally.

2084
01:53:17,817 --> 01:53:19,142
“Oh, him!

2085
01:53:19,142 --> 01:53:23,472
He weren’t raised where
he could see petticoats.

2086
01:53:23,472 --> 01:53:23,872
Mrs.

2087
01:53:23,872 --> 01:53:28,845
Henry she come hyeh from the railroad
with the Judge afteh dark.

2088
01:53:28,845 --> 01:53:32,802
Next mawnin’ early she walked out to view
her new home, and the rooster was a-

2089
01:53:32,802 --> 01:53:35,098
feedin’ by the door, and he seen her.

2090
01:53:35,098 --> 01:53:38,953
Well, seh, he screeched that awful I run
out of the bunk-house;

2091
01:53:38,953 --> 01:53:42,554
and he jus’ went over the fence and took
down Sunk Creek shoutin’

2092
01:53:42,554 --> 01:53:44,003
fire, right along.

2093
01:53:44,003 --> -1:59:59,000
He has never come back.

2094
-1:59:59,000 --> 00:00:02,000
”

2095
01:53:48,748 --> 01:53:55,010
“There’s a hen over there now that has no
judgment,” I said, indicating Em’ly.

2096
01:53:55,010 --> 01:53:58,954
She had got herself outside the house,
and was on the bars of a corral,

2097
01:53:58,954 --> 01:54:02,580
her vociferations reduced
to an occasional squawk.

2098
01:54:02,580 --> 01:54:04,756
I told him about the potatoes.

2099
01:54:04,756 --> 01:54:08,193
“I never knowed her name before,” said he.

2100
01:54:08,193 --> 01:54:11,641
“That runaway rooster, he hated her.

2101
01:54:11,641 --> 01:54:13,895
And she hated him same as
she hates ’em all.”

2102
01:54:13,895 --> 01:54:16,490
“I named her myself,”
said I, “after I came

2103
01:54:16,490 --> 01:54:18,787
to notice her particularly.

2104
01:54:18,787 --> 01:54:22,392
There’s an old maid at home who’s
charitable, and belongs to the Cruelty

2105
01:54:22,392 --> 01:54:26,765
to Animals, and she never knows whether
she had better cross in front of a

2106
01:54:26,765 --> 01:54:28,646
street car or wait.

2107
01:54:28,646 --> 01:54:31,166
I named the hen after her.

2108
01:54:31,166 --> 01:54:32,802
Does she ever lay eggs?”

2109
01:54:32,802 --> 01:54:37,571
The Virginian had not “troubled his
haid” over the poultry.

2110
01:54:37,571 --> 01:54:39,905
“Well, I don’t believe she knows how.

2111
01:54:39,905 --> 01:54:41,911
I think she came near being a rooster.”

2112
01:54:41,911 --> 01:54:45,143
“She’s sure manly-lookin’,”
said the Virginian.

2113
01:54:45,143 --> 01:54:48,116
We had walked toward the corral,
and he was now scrutinizing

2114
01:54:48,116 --> 01:54:49,097
Em’ly with interest.

2115
01:54:49,097 --> 01:54:51,050
She was an egregious fowl.

2116
01:54:51,050 --> 01:54:54,733
She was huge and gaunt,
with great yellow beak,

2117
01:54:54,733 --> 01:54:58,268
and she stood straight and alert in the
manner of responsible people.

2118
01:54:58,268 --> 01:55:00,450
There was something wrong with her tail.

2119
01:55:00,450 --> 01:55:04,082
It slanted far to one side,
one feather in it twice as

2120
01:55:04,082 --> 01:55:05,263
long as the rest.

2121
01:55:05,263 --> 01:55:07,577
Feathers on her breast there were none.

2122
01:55:07,577 --> 01:55:12,918
These had been worn entirely off by her
habit of sitting upon potatoes and

2123
01:55:12,918 --> 01:55:15,460
other rough abnormal objects.

2124
01:55:15,460 --> 01:55:22,887
And this lent to her appearance an air of
being décollete, singularly at variance

2125
01:55:22,887 --> 01:55:26,516
with her otherwise prudish ensemble.

2126
01:55:26,516 --> 01:55:31,442
Her eye was remarkably bright,
but somehow it had an

2127
01:55:31,442 --> 01:55:32,925
outraged expression.

2128
01:55:32,925 --> 01:55:39,135
It was as if she went about the world
perpetually scandalized over the doings

2129
01:55:39,135 --> 01:55:41,266
that fell beneath her notice.

2130
01:55:41,266 --> 01:55:45,595
Her legs were blue, long,
and remarkably stout.

2131
01:55:45,595 --> 01:55:49,672
“She’d ought to wear knickerbockers,”
murmured the Virginian.

2132
01:55:49,672 --> 01:55:53,258
“She’d look a heap better ’n some
o’ them college students.

2133
01:55:53,258 --> -1:59:59,000
And she’ll set on potatoes, yu’ say?

2134
-1:59:59,000 --> 00:00:02,000
”

2135
01:55:55,404 --> 01:55:59,049
“She thinks she can hatch out anything.

2136
01:55:59,049 --> 01:56:02,557
I’ve found her with onions,
and last Tuesday I caught her on

2137
01:56:02,557 --> -1:59:59,000
two balls of soap.

2138
-1:59:59,000 --> 00:00:02,000
”

2139
01:56:03,997 --> 01:56:09,400
In the afternoon the tall cowpuncher and
I rode out to get an antelope.

2140
01:56:09,400 --> 01:56:12,933
After an hour, during which he was
completely taciturn,

2141
01:56:12,933 --> 01:56:18,695
he said: “I reckon maybe this hyeh
lonesome country ain’t been healthy for

2142
01:56:18,695 --> 01:56:19,751
Em’ly to live in.

2143
01:56:19,751 --> 01:56:21,490
It ain’t for some humans.

2144
01:56:21,490 --> 01:56:25,265
Them old trappers in the mountains gets
skewed in the haid mighty often,

2145
01:56:25,265 --> 01:56:28,787
an’ talks out loud when nobody’s nigher
’n a hundred miles.”

2146
01:56:28,787 --> 01:56:31,579
“Em’ly has not been solitary,” I replied.

2147
01:56:31,579 --> 01:56:33,078
“There are forty chickens here.”

2148
01:56:33,078 --> 01:56:34,744
“That’s so,” said he.

2149
01:56:34,744 --> 01:56:36,047
“It don’t explain her.”

2150
01:56:36,047 --> 01:56:39,586
He fell silent again,
riding beside me, easy and

2151
01:56:39,586 --> 01:56:42,159
indolent in the saddle.

2152
01:56:42,159 --> 01:56:48,773
His long figure looked so loose and inert
that the swift, light spring he made to

2153
01:56:48,773 --> 01:56:51,146
the ground seemed an impossible feat.

2154
01:56:51,146 --> 01:56:54,111
He had seen an antelope where I saw none.

2155
01:56:54,111 --> 01:56:57,423
“Take a shot yourself,”
I urged him, as he motioned

2156
01:56:57,423 --> 01:56:58,423
me to be quick.

2157
01:56:58,423 --> 01:57:00,363
“You never shoot when I’m with you.”

2158
01:57:00,363 --> 01:57:03,355
“I ain’t hyeh for that,” he answered.

2159
01:57:03,355 --> 01:57:05,494
“Now you’ve let him get away on yu’!”

2160
01:57:05,494 --> 01:57:07,506
The antelope had in truth departed.

2161
01:57:07,506 --> 01:57:11,847
“Why,” he said to my protest,
“I can hit them things any day.

2162
01:57:11,847 --> 01:57:13,795
What’s your notion as to Em’ly?”

2163
01:57:13,795 --> 01:57:16,716
“I can’t account for her,” I replied.

2164
01:57:16,716 --> 01:57:19,868
“Well,” he said musingly,
and then his mind took one of those

2165
01:57:19,868 --> 01:57:23,867
particular turns that made me love him,
“Taylor ought to see her.

2166
01:57:23,867 --> 01:57:26,320
She’d be just the schoolmarm
for Bear Creek!”

2167
01:57:26,320 --> 01:57:30,191
“She’s not much like the eating-house
lady at Medicine Bow,” I said.

2168
01:57:30,191 --> 01:57:31,858
He gave a hilarious chuckle.

2169
01:57:31,858 --> 01:57:34,720
“No, Em’ly knows nothing o’ them joys.

2170
01:57:34,720 --> 01:57:36,560
So yu’ have no notion about her?

2171
01:57:36,560 --> 01:57:38,375
Well, I’ve got one.

2172
01:57:38,375 --> 01:57:41,773
I reckon maybe she was hatched
after a big thunderstorm.”

2173
01:57:41,773 --> 01:57:43,681
“In a big thunderstorm!”

2174
01:57:43,681 --> 01:57:44,966
I exclaimed.

2175
01:57:44,966 --> 01:57:45,842
“Yes.

2176
01:57:45,842 --> 01:57:49,163
Don’t yu’ know about them,
and what they’ll do to aiggs?

2177
01:57:49,163 --> 01:57:53,704
A big case o’ lightnin’ and thunder will
addle aiggs and keep ’em from hatchin’.

2178
01:57:53,704 --> 01:57:56,864
And I expect one came along,
and all the other aiggs of Em’ly’s set

2179
01:57:56,864 --> 01:58:00,647
didn’t hatch out, but got plumb addled,
and she happened not to get addled that

2180
01:58:00,647 --> 01:58:02,940
far, and so she just managed
to make it through.

2181
01:58:02,940 --> 01:58:05,486
But she cert’nly ain’t got a strong haid.”

2182
01:58:05,486 --> 01:58:07,416
“I fear she has not,” said I.

2183
01:58:07,416 --> 01:58:10,633
“Mighty hon’ble intentions,” he observed.

2184
01:58:10,633 --> 01:58:14,969
“If she can’t make out to lay anything,
she wants to hatch somethin’, and

2185
01:58:14,969 --> 01:58:16,340
be a mother anyways.”

2186
01:58:16,340 --> 01:58:22,871
“I wonder what relation the law considers
that a hen is to the chicken she hatched

2187
01:58:22,871 --> 01:58:24,199
but did not lay?”

2188
01:58:24,199 --> 01:58:24,977
I inquired.

2189
01:58:24,977 --> 01:58:29,179
The Virginian made no reply
to this frivolous suggestion.

2190
01:58:29,179 --> 01:58:33,899
He was gazing over the wide landscape
gravely and with apparent inattention.

2191
01:58:33,899 --> 01:58:38,728
He invariably saw game before I did,
and was off his horse and crouched among

2192
01:58:38,728 --> 01:58:42,890
the sage while I was still getting my
left foot clear of the stirrup.

2193
01:58:42,890 --> 01:58:46,091
I succeeded in killing an antelope,
and we rode home with the

2194
01:58:46,091 --> 01:58:48,692
head and hind quarters.

2195
01:58:48,692 --> 01:58:50,733
“No,” said he.

2196
01:58:50,733 --> 01:58:54,943
“It’s sure the thunder,
and not the lonesomeness.

2197
01:58:54,943 --> 01:58:57,880
How do yu’ like the lonesomeness
yourself?”

2198
01:58:57,880 --> 01:58:59,913
I told him that I liked it.

2199
01:58:59,913 --> 01:59:03,052
“I could not live without
it now,” he said.

2200
01:59:03,052 --> 01:59:04,759
“This has got into my system.”

2201
01:59:04,759 --> 01:59:07,534
He swept his hand out at the
vast space of world.

2202
01:59:07,534 --> 01:59:11,693
“I went back home to see my folks onced.

2203
01:59:11,693 --> 01:59:14,722
Mother was dyin’ slow, and she wanted me.

2204
01:59:14,722 --> 01:59:16,037
I stayed a year.

2205
01:59:16,037 --> 01:59:19,356
But them Virginia mountains could
please me no more.

2206
01:59:19,356 --> 01:59:24,100
Afteh she was gone, I told my
brothers and sisters goodbye.

2207
01:59:24,100 --> 01:59:27,106
We like each other well enough,
but I reckon I’ll not go back.”

2208
01:59:27,106 --> 01:59:31,153
We found Em’ly seated upon a collection
of green California peaches,

2209
01:59:31,153 --> 01:59:33,196
which the Judge had brought
from the railroad.

2210
01:59:33,196 --> 01:59:36,312
“I don’t mind her any more,”
I said; “I’m sorry for her.”

2211
01:59:36,312 --> 01:59:39,405
“I’ve been sorry for her right
along,” said the Virginian.

2212
01:59:39,405 --> 01:59:42,453
“She does hate the roosters so.”

2213
01:59:42,453 --> 01:59:47,882
And he said that he was making a
collection of every class of object

2214
01:59:47,882 --> 01:59:50,864
which he found her treating as eggs.

2215
01:59:50,864 --> 01:59:55,747
But Em’ly’s egg-industry was terminated
abruptly one morning,

2216
01:59:55,747 --> 01:59:58,667
and her unquestioned energies diverted
to a new channel.

2217
01:59:58,667 --> 02:00:02,227
A turkey which had been sitting in the
root-house appeared with twelve

2218
02:00:02,227 --> 02:00:06,929
children, and a family of
bantams occurred almost simultaneously.

2219
02:00:06,929 --> 02:00:11,690
Em’ly was importantly scratching the soil
inside Paladin’s corral when the bantam

2220
02:00:11,690 --> 02:00:15,249
tribe of newly born came by down the
lane, and she caught sight of

2221
02:00:15,249 --> 02:00:16,740
them through the bars.

2222
02:00:16,740 --> 02:00:20,951
She crossed the corral at a run,
and intercepted two of the chicks that

2223
02:00:20,951 --> 02:00:23,864
were trailing somewhat
behind their real mamma.

2224
02:00:23,864 --> 02:00:28,552
These she undertook to appropriate,
and assumed a high tone with the bantam,

2225
02:00:28,552 --> 02:00:31,358
who was the smaller,
and hence obliged to retreat with

2226
02:00:31,358 --> 02:00:33,977
her still numerous family.

2227
02:00:33,977 --> 02:00:38,414
I interfered, and put matters straight;
but the adjustment was only temporary.

2228
02:00:38,414 --> 02:00:43,776
In an hour I saw Em’ly immensely busy
with two more bantams,

2229
02:00:43,776 --> 02:00:48,431
leading them about and taking a care of
them which I must admit

2230
02:00:48,431 --> 02:00:50,812
seemed perfectly efficient.

2231
02:00:50,812 --> 02:00:56,774
And now came the first incident that made
me suspect her to be demented.

2232
02:00:56,774 --> 02:01:00,433
She had proceeded with her changelings
behind the kitchen, where one of the

2233
02:01:00,433 --> 02:01:05,034
irrigation ditches ran under the fence
from the hayfield to supply

2234
02:01:05,034 --> 02:01:06,785
the house with water.

2235
02:01:06,785 --> 02:01:13,367
Some distance along this ditch inside the
field were the twelve turkeys in the

2236
02:01:13,367 --> 02:01:16,908
short, recently cut stubble.

2237
02:01:16,908 --> 02:01:20,414
Again Em’ly set off instantly like a deer.

2238
02:01:20,414 --> 02:01:23,938
She left the dismayed bantams behind her.

2239
02:01:23,938 --> 02:01:28,205
She crossed the ditch with one jump of
her stout blue legs,

2240
02:01:28,205 --> 02:01:31,831
flew over the grass,
and was at once among the turkeys,

2241
02:01:31,831 --> 02:01:37,423
where, with an instinct of maternity as
undiscriminating as it was reckless,

2242
02:01:37,423 --> 02:01:40,837
she attempted to huddle
some of them away.

2243
02:01:40,837 --> 02:01:45,314
But this other mamma was not a bantam,
and in a few moments Em’ly was entirely

2244
02:01:45,314 --> 02:01:49,240
routed in her attempt to acquire a
new variety of family.

2245
02:01:49,240 --> 02:01:54,137
This spectacle was witnessed by the
Virginian and myself,

2246
02:01:54,137 --> 02:01:55,354
and it overcame him.

2247
02:01:55,354 --> 02:02:00,038
He went speechless across to the bunk-
house, by himself, and sat on his bed,

2248
02:02:00,038 --> 02:02:04,108
while I took the abandoned bantams back
to their own circle.

2249
02:02:04,108 --> 02:02:10,207
I have often wondered what the other
fowls thought of all this.

2250
02:02:10,207 --> 02:02:13,585
Some impression it certainly
did make upon them.

2251
02:02:13,585 --> 02:02:19,485
The notion may seem out of reason to
those who have never closely attended to

2252
02:02:19,485 --> 02:02:24,047
other animals than man;
but I am convinced that any community

2253
02:02:24,047 --> 02:02:28,434
which shares some of our instincts will
share some of the resulting feelings,

2254
02:02:28,434 --> 02:02:32,190
and that birds and beasts have
conventions, the breach

2255
02:02:32,190 --> 02:02:33,630
of which startles them.

2256
02:02:33,630 --> 02:02:36,987
If there be anything in evolution,
this would seem inevitable.

2257
02:02:36,987 --> 02:02:42,776
At all events, the chicken-house was
upset during the following several days.

2258
02:02:42,776 --> 02:02:47,325
Em’ly disturbed now the bantams and now
the turkeys, and several of these latter

2259
02:02:47,325 --> 02:02:51,047
had died, though I will not go so far as
to say that this was the result

2260
02:02:51,047 --> 02:02:53,067
of her misplaced attentions.

2261
02:02:53,067 --> 02:02:57,697
Nevertheless, I was seriously thinking of
locking her up till the broods should be

2262
02:02:57,697 --> 02:03:02,489
a little older, when another event
happened, and all was suddenly at peace.

2263
02:03:02,489 --> 02:03:06,574
The Judge’s setter came in one
morning, wagging her tail.

2264
02:03:06,574 --> 02:03:10,113
She had had her puppies,
and she now took us to where they were

2265
02:03:10,113 --> 02:03:15,394
housed, in between the floor of a
building and the hollow ground.

2266
02:03:15,394 --> 02:03:18,069
Em’ly was seated on the whole litter.

2267
02:03:18,069 --> 02:03:21,821
“No,” I said to the Judge,
“I am not surprised.

2268
02:03:21,821 --> 02:03:23,415
She is capable of anything.”

2269
02:03:23,415 --> 02:03:27,232
In her new choice of offspring,
this hen had at length

2270
02:03:27,232 --> 02:03:29,152
encountered an unworthy parent.

2271
02:03:29,152 --> 02:03:33,261
The setter was bored by her own puppies.

2272
02:03:33,261 --> 02:03:39,591
She found the hole under the house an
obscure and monotonous residence

2273
02:03:39,591 --> 02:03:43,361
compared with the dining room,
and our company more stimulating and

2274
02:03:43,361 --> 02:03:46,135
sympathetic than that of her children.

2275
02:03:46,135 --> 02:03:51,857
A much-petted contact with our superior
race had developed her dog intelligence

2276
02:03:51,857 --> 02:03:55,217
above its natural level,
and turned her into an unnatural,

2277
02:03:55,217 --> 02:03:58,577
neglectful mother, who was constantly
forgetting her nursery

2278
02:03:58,577 --> 02:04:00,285
for worldly pleasures.

2279
02:04:00,285 --> 02:04:03,983
At certain periods of the day she
repaired to the puppies and fed them,

2280
02:04:03,983 --> 02:04:07,162
but came away when this perfunctory
ceremony was accomplished;

2281
02:04:07,162 --> 02:04:09,747
and she was glad enough to have a
governess bring them up.

2282
02:04:09,747 --> 02:04:12,418
She made no quarrel with Em’ly,
and the two understood

2283
02:04:12,418 --> 02:04:13,718
each other perfectly.

2284
02:04:13,718 --> 02:04:18,066
I have never seen among animals any
arrangement so civilized

2285
02:04:18,066 --> 02:04:19,759
and so perverted.

2286
02:04:19,759 --> 02:04:21,707
It made Em’ly perfectly happy.

2287
02:04:21,707 --> 02:04:26,247
To see her sitting all day jealously
spreading her wings over some blind

2288
02:04:26,247 --> 02:04:30,870
puppies was sufficiently curious;
but when they became large enough to

2289
02:04:30,870 --> 02:04:35,297
come out from under the house and toddle
about in the proud hen’s wake,

2290
02:04:35,297 --> 02:04:39,439
I longed for some distinguished
naturalist.

