2651
02:27:05,511 --> 02:27:11,810
Later she stated to a friend that she had
always thought the Episcopal Church a

2652
02:27:11,810 --> 02:27:14,585
snobbish one, and now she knew it.

2653
02:27:14,585 --> 02:27:19,669
So public opinion went on being
indignant over Molly’s conduct.

2654
02:27:19,669 --> 02:27:23,296
She could stoop to work for money,
and yet she pretended to hold herself

2655
02:27:23,296 --> 02:27:28,918
above the most rising young man in
Hoosic Falls, and all just because there

2656
02:27:28,918 --> 02:27:31,795
was a difference in their grandmothers!

2657
02:27:31,795 --> 02:27:35,702
Was this the reason at the bottom of it?

2658
02:27:35,702 --> 02:27:37,455
The very bottom?

2659
02:27:37,455 --> 02:27:41,865
I cannot be certain, because I have never
been a girl myself.

2660
02:27:41,865 --> 02:27:45,906
Perhaps she thought that work is not a
stooping, and that marriage may be.

2661
02:27:45,906 --> 02:27:50,945
Perhaps⁠—But all I really know is that
Molly Wood continued cheerfully to

2662
02:27:50,945 --> 02:27:54,836
embroider the handkerchiefs,
make the preserves, teach the pupils⁠—

2663
02:27:54,836 --> 02:27:57,676
and firmly to reject Sam Bannett.

2664
02:27:57,676 --> 02:28:00,704
Thus it went on until she was twenty.

2665
02:28:00,704 --> 02:28:05,297
There certain members of her family began
to tell her how rich Sam was going to

2666
02:28:05,297 --> 02:28:07,640
be⁠—was, indeed, already.

2667
02:28:07,640 --> 02:28:14,900
It was at this time that she wrote Mrs.
Balaam her doubts and her desires as to

2668
02:28:14,900 --> 02:28:16,740
migrating to Bear Creek.

2669
02:28:16,740 --> 02:28:20,780
It was at this time also that her face
grew a little paler,

2670
02:28:20,780 --> 02:28:25,535
and her friends thought that she was
overworked, and Mrs. Flynt feared she

2671
02:28:25,535 --> 02:28:26,631
was losing her looks.

2672
02:28:26,631 --> 02:28:29,795
It was at this time, too,
that she grew very intimate with that

2673
02:28:29,795 --> 02:28:32,845
great-aunt over at Dunbarton,
