02:45:30,659 --> 02:45:33,966
“They,” was how he put
it to his acquaintances.

2948
02:45:33,966 --> 02:45:37,862
His acquaintances did not know that he
had bought himself a pair of trousers

2949
02:45:37,862 --> 02:45:41,820
and a scarf, unnecessarily excellent for
such a general visit.

2950
02:45:41,820 --> 02:45:46,053
They did not know that in the spring,
two days after the adventure with the

2951
02:45:46,053 --> 02:45:51,394
stage, he had learned accidentally who
the lady in the stage was.

2952
02:45:51,394 --> 02:45:56,259
This he had kept to himself;
nor did the camp ever notice that he had

2953
02:45:56,259 --> 02:46:01,720
ceased to sing that eightieth stanza he
had made about the A.B.C.

2954
02:46:01,720 --> 02:46:04,135
⁠—the stanza which was not printable.

2955
02:46:04,135 --> 02:46:09,578
He effaced it imperceptibly,
giving the boys the other seventy-

2956
02:46:09,578 --> 02:46:12,450
nine at judicious intervals.

2957
02:46:12,450 --> 02:46:16,326
They dreamed of no guile,
but merely saw in him,

2958
02:46:16,326 --> 02:46:22,477
whether frequenting camp or town,
the same not over-angelic comrade whom

2959
02:46:22,477 --> 02:46:24,888
they valued and could
not wholly understand.

2960
02:46:24,888 --> 02:46:29,833
All spring he had ridden trail,
worked at ditches during summer,

2961
02:46:29,833 --> 02:46:32,398
and now he had just finished
with the beef roundup.

2962
02:46:32,398 --> 02:46:37,313
Yesterday, while he was spending a little
comfortable money at the Drybone hog-

2963
02:46:37,313 --> 02:46:42,096
ranch, a casual traveller from the north
gossiped of Bear Creek,

2964
02:46:42,096 --> 02:46:47,683
and the fences up there,
and the farm crops, the Westfalls,

2965
02:46:47,683 --> 02:46:53,258
and the young schoolmarm from Vermont,
for whom the Taylors had built a cabin

2966
02:46:53,258 --> 02:46:54,950
next door to theirs.

2967
02:46:54,950 --> 02:46:58,489
The traveller had not seen her,
but Mrs. Taylor and all the ladies

2968
02:46:58,489 --> 02:47:02,877
thought the world of her,
and Lin McLean had told him she was

2969
02:47:02,877 --> 02:47:05,452
“away up in G.”

2970
02:47:05,452 --> 02:47:08,943
She would have plenty of partners
at this Swinton barbecue.

2971
02:47:08,943 --> 02:47:13,929
Great boon for the country,
wasn’t it, steers jumping that way?

2972
02:47:13,929 --> 02:47:19,675
The Virginian heard, asking no questions;
and left town in an hour,

2973
02:47:19,675 --> 02:47:24,051
with the scarf and trousers tied in his
slicker behind his saddle.

2974
02:47:24,051 --> 02:47:28,810
After looking upon the ford again,
even though it was dry and not at all

2975
02:47:28,810 --> 02:47:32,167
the same place, he journeyed
in attentively.

2976
02:47:32,167 --> 02:47:35,246
When you have been hard at work for
months with no time to think,

2977
02:47:35,246 --> 02:47:38,405
of course you think a great deal during
your first empty days.

2978
02:47:38,405 --> 02:47:41,524
“Step along, you Monte hawss!”

2979
02:47:41,524 --> 02:47:45,190
he said, rousing after some while.

2980
02:47:45,190 --> 02:47:47,939
He disciplined Monte,
who flattened his ears

2981
02:47:47,939 --> 02:47:50,444
affectedly and snorted.

2982
02:47:50,444 --> 02:47:54,582
“Why, you surely ain’ thinkin’ of you’-
self as a hero?

2983
02:47:54,582 --> 02:47:57,265
She wasn’t really a-drowndin’,
you pie-biter.”

2984
02:47:57,265 --> 02:48:00,071
He rested his serious
glance upon the alkali.

2985
02:48:00,071 --> 02:48:05,560
“She’s not likely to have forgot
that mix-up, though.

2986
02:48:05,560 --> 02:48:11,469
I guess I’ll not remind her about
grippin’ me, and all that.

2987
02:48:11,469 --> 02:48:15,019
She wasn’t the kind a man ought to
josh about such things.

2988
02:48:15,019 --> 02:48:17,208
She had a right clear eye.”

2989
02:48:17,208 --> 02:48:22,854
Thus, tall and loose in the saddle,
did he jog along the sixty miles which

2990
02:48:22,854 --> 02:48:25,845
still lay between him and the dance.

2991
02:48:25,845 --> 02:48:26,570
CHAPTER X

2992
02:48:26,570 --> 02:48:27,805
Where Fancy Was Bred

2993
02:48:27,805 --> 02:48:31,898
Two camps in the open,
and the Virginian’s Monte horse,

2994
02:48:31,898 --> 02:48:36,072
untired, brought him to the Swintons’ in
good time for the barbecue.

2995
02:48:36,072 --> 02:48:39,513
The horse received good food at length,
while his rider was welcomed

2996
02:48:39,513 --> 02:48:40,672
with good whiskey.

2997
02:48:40,672 --> 02:48:44,719
Good whiskey⁠—for had not steers
jumped to seventy-five?

2998
02:48:44,719 --> 02:48:49,397
Inside the Goose Egg kitchen many small
delicacies were preparing,

2999
02:48:49,397 --> 02:48:52,283
and a steer was roasting whole outside.

3000
02:48:52,283 --> 02:48:56,965
The bed of flame under it showed steadily
brighter against the dusk that was

3001
02:48:56,965 --> 02:48:59,058
beginning to veil the lowlands.

3002
02:48:59,058 --> 02:49:05,244
The busy hosts went and came,
while men stood and men lay

3003
02:49:05,244 --> 02:49:06,635
near the fire-glow.

3004
02:49:06,635 --> 02:49:11,381
Chalkeye was there, and Nebrasky,
and Trampas, and Honey Wiggin,

3005
02:49:11,381 --> 02:49:16,065
with others, enjoying the occasion;
but Honey Wiggin was enjoying himself:

3006
02:49:16,065 --> 02:49:19,518
he had an audience; he was sitting
up discoursing to it.

3007
02:49:19,518 --> 02:49:20,120
“Hello!”

3008
02:49:20,120 --> 02:49:22,235
he said, perceiving the Virginian.

3009
02:49:22,235 --> 02:49:25,127
“So you’ve dropped in for your turn!

3010
02:49:25,127 --> 02:49:28,871
Number⁠—six, ain’t he, boys?”

3011
02:49:28,871 --> 02:49:33,516
“Depends who’s a-runnin’ the countin’,”
said the Virginian, and stretched

3012
02:49:33,516 --> 02:49:35,697
himself down among the audience.

3013
02:49:35,697 --> 02:49:41,132
“I’ve saw him number one when nobody else
was around,” said Trampas.

3014
02:49:41,132 --> 02:49:44,356
“How far away was you standin’
when you beheld that?”

3015
02:49:44,356 --> 02:49:46,111
inquired the lounging Southerner.

3016
02:49:46,111 --> 02:49:51,156
“Well, boys,” said Wiggin,
“I expect it will be Miss Schoolmarm

3017
02:49:51,156 --> 02:49:53,686
says who’s number one tonight.”

3018
02:49:53,686 --> 02:49:56,342
“So she’s arrived in this hyeh country?”

3019
02:49:56,342 --> 02:49:58,526
observed the Virginian, very casually.

3020
02:49:58,526 --> 02:49:59,683
“Arrived!”

3021
02:49:59,683 --> 02:50:01,292
said Trampas again.

3022
02:50:01,292 --> 02:50:03,002
“Where have you been grazing lately?”

3023
02:50:03,002 --> 02:50:06,043
“A right smart way from the mules.”

3024
02:50:06,043 --> 02:50:10,785
“Nebrasky and the boys was tellin’ me
they’d missed yu’ off the

3025
02:50:10,785 --> 02:50:14,152
range,” again interposed Wiggin.

3026
02:50:14,152 --> 02:50:19,392
“Say, Nebrasky, who have yu’ offered your
canary to the schoolmarm said

3027
02:50:19,392 --> 02:50:20,512
you mustn’t give her?”

3028
02:50:20,512 --> 02:50:22,595
Nebrasky grinned wretchedly.

3029
02:50:22,595 --> 02:50:27,986
“Well, she’s a lady, and she’s square,
not takin’ a man’s gift when she

3030
02:50:27,986 --> 02:50:29,368
don’t take the man.

3031
02:50:29,368 --> 02:50:32,663
But you’d ought to get back all them
letters yu’ wrote her.

3032
02:50:32,663 --> -1:59:59,000
Yu’ sure ought to ask
her for them telltales.

3033
-1:59:59,000 --> 00:00:02,000
”

3034
02:50:36,243 --> 02:50:39,013
“Ah, pshaw, Honey!”

3035
02:50:39,013 --> 02:50:40,432
protested the youth.

3036
02:50:40,432 --> 02:50:43,819
It was well known that he could
not write his name.

3037
02:50:43,819 --> 02:50:46,182
“Why, if here ain’t Bokay Baldy!”

3038
02:50:46,182 --> 02:50:49,943
cried the agile Wiggin,
stooping to fresh prey.

3039
02:50:49,943 --> 02:50:52,408
“Found them slippers yet, Baldy?

3040
02:50:52,408 --> 02:50:56,862
Tell yu’ boys, that was turruble
sad luck Baldy had.

3041
02:50:56,862 --> 02:50:58,010
Did yu’ hear about that?

3042
02:50:58,010 --> 02:51:03,974
Baldy, yu’ know, he can stay on a tame
horse most as well as the schoolmarm.

3043
02:51:03,974 --> 02:51:07,779
But just you give him a pair of young
knittin’-needles and see

3044
02:51:07,779 --> 02:51:09,039
him make ’em sweat!

3045
02:51:09,039 --> 02:51:13,702
He worked an elegant pair of slippers
with pink cabbages on ’em for Miss

3046
02:51:13,702 --> 02:51:14,319
Wood.”

3047
02:51:14,319 --> 02:51:17,426
“I bought ’em at Medicine
Bow,” blundered Baldy.

3048
02:51:17,426 --> 02:51:18,618
“So yu’ did!”

3049
02:51:18,618 --> 02:51:21,044
assented the skilful comedian.

3050
02:51:21,044 --> 02:51:23,691
“Baldy he bought ’em.

3051
02:51:23,691 --> 02:51:29,507
And on the road to her cabin there at the
Taylors’ he got thinkin’ they might be

3052
02:51:29,507 --> 02:51:33,033
too big, and he got studyin’ what to do.

3053
02:51:33,033 --> 02:51:36,421
And he fixed up to tell her about his not
bein’ sure of the size,

3054
02:51:36,421 --> 02:51:41,189
and how she was to let him know if they
dropped off her, and he’d exchange ’em,

3055
02:51:41,189 --> 02:51:45,238
and when he got right near her door,
why, he couldn’t find his courage.

3056
02:51:45,238 --> 02:51:50,137
And so he slips the parcel under the
fence and starts serenadin’ her.

3057
02:51:50,137 --> 02:51:54,338
But she ain’t inside her cabin at all.

3058
02:51:54,338 --> 02:51:59,135
She’s at supper next door with the
Taylors, and Baldy singin’ ‘Love has

3059
02:51:59,135 --> 02:52:02,706
conqwered pride and angwer’
to a lone house.

3060
02:52:02,706 --> 02:52:07,829
Lin McLean was comin’ up by Taylor’s
corral, where Taylor’s Texas bull was.

3061
02:52:07,829 --> 02:52:10,872
Well, it was turruble sad.

3062
02:52:10,872 --> 02:52:15,493
Baldy’s pants got tore,
but he fell inside the fence,

3063
02:52:15,493 --> 02:52:20,181
and Lin druv the bull back and somebody
stole them Medicine Bow galoshes.

3064
02:52:20,181 --> -1:59:59,000
Are you goin’ to knit
her some more, Bokay?

3065
-1:59:59,000 --> 00:00:02,000
”

3066
02:52:22,343 --> 02:52:27,311
“About half that ain’t straight,”
Baldy commented, with mildness.

3067
02:52:27,311 --> 02:52:31,081
“The half that was tore off yer pants?

3068
02:52:31,081 --> 02:52:34,580
Well, never mind, Baldy;
Lin will get left too,

3069
02:52:34,580 --> 02:52:36,167
same as all of yu’.”

3070
02:52:36,167 --> 02:52:37,704
“Is there many?”

3071
02:52:37,704 --> 02:52:38,981
inquired the Virginian.

3072
02:52:38,981 --> 02:52:42,712
He was still stretched on his back,
looking up at the sky.

3073
02:52:42,712 --> 02:52:47,039
“I don’t know how many she’s been used to
where she was raised,” Wiggin answered.

3074
02:52:47,039 --> 02:52:51,456
“A kid stage-driver come from Point of
Rocks one day and went back the next.

3075
02:52:51,456 --> 02:52:56,517
Then the foreman of the 76 outfit,
and the horse-wrangler from the Bar-

3076
02:52:56,517 --> 02:53:02,025
Circle-L, and two deputy marshals,
with punchers, stringin’ right along⁠—

3077
02:53:02,025 --> 02:53:03,702
all got their tumble.

3078
02:53:03,702 --> 02:53:09,134
Old Judge Burrage from Cheyenne come up
in August for a hunt and stayed round

3079
02:53:09,134 --> 02:53:11,003
here and never hunted at all.

3080
02:53:11,003 --> 02:53:13,662
There was that horse thief⁠—
awful good-lookin’.

3081
02:53:13,662 --> 02:53:17,655
Taylor wanted to warn her about him,
but Mrs. Taylor said she’d look after

3082
02:53:17,655 --> 02:53:18,934
her if it was needed.

3083
02:53:18,934 --> 02:53:19,454
Mr.

3084
02:53:19,454 --> 02:53:24,767
Horse-thief gave it up quicker than most;
but the schoolmarm couldn’t have knowed

3085
02:53:24,767 --> 02:53:29,080
he had a Mrs. Horse-thief camped on
Poison Spider till afterwards.

3086
02:53:29,080 --> 02:53:30,782
She wouldn’t go ridin’ with him.

3087
02:53:30,782 --> -1:59:59,000
She’ll go with some, takin’ a kid along.

3088
-1:59:59,000 --> 00:00:02,000
”

3089
02:53:33,712 --> 02:53:34,473
“Bah!”

3090
02:53:34,473 --> 02:53:36,521
said Trampas.

3091
02:53:36,521 --> 02:53:41,064
The Virginian stopped looking at the sky,
and watched Trampas from where he lay.

3092
02:53:41,064 --> 02:53:45,534
“I think she encourages a man
some,” said poor Nebrasky.

3093
02:53:45,534 --> 02:53:46,976
“Encourages?

3094
02:53:46,976 --> 02:53:50,796
Because she lets yu’ teach her how
to shoot,” said Wiggin.

3095
02:53:50,796 --> 02:53:53,211
“Well⁠—I don’t guess I’m a judge.

3096
02:53:53,211 --> 02:53:56,931
I’ve always kind o’ kep’ away
from them good women.

3097
02:53:56,931 --> 02:54:00,410
Don’t seem to think of anything to
chat about to ’em.

3098
02:54:00,410 --> 02:54:03,896
The only folks I’d say she encourages
is the school kids.

3099
02:54:03,896 --> 02:54:05,248
She kisses them.”

3100
02:54:05,248 --> 02:54:09,230
“Riding and shooting and kissing
the kids,” sneered Trampas.

3101
02:54:09,230 --> 02:54:11,810
“That’s a heap too pussy-kitten for me.”

3102
02:54:11,810 --> 02:54:12,759
They laughed.

3103
02:54:12,759 --> 02:54:16,030
The sagebrush audience is readily cynical.

3104
02:54:16,030 --> 02:54:18,865
“Look for the man, I say,”
Trampas pursued.

3105
02:54:18,865 --> 02:54:20,258
“And ain’t he there?

3106
02:54:20,258 --> 02:54:25,223
She leaves Baldy sit on the fence while
she and Lin McLean⁠—”

3107
02:54:25,223 --> 02:54:28,689
They laughed loudly at the blackguard
picture which he drew;

3108
02:54:28,689 --> 02:54:33,421
and the laugh stopped short,
for the Virginian stood over Trampas.

3109
02:54:33,421 --> 02:54:37,446
“You can rise up now,
and tell them you lie,” he said.

3110
02:54:37,446 --> 02:54:40,977
The man was still for a moment
in the dead silence.

3111
02:54:40,977 --> 02:54:45,012
“I thought you claimed you and her wasn’t
acquainted,” said he then.

3112
02:54:45,012 --> 02:54:48,867
“Stand on your laigs,
you polecat, and say you’re a liar!”

3113
02:54:48,867 --> 02:54:50,811
Trampas’s hand moved behind him.

3114
02:54:50,811 --> 02:54:55,143
“Quit that,” said the Southerner,
“or I’ll break your neck!”

3115
02:54:55,143 --> 02:54:58,337
The eye of a man is the
prince of deadly weapons.

3116
02:54:58,337 --> 02:55:02,729
Trampas looked in the
Virginian’s, and slowly rose.

3117
02:55:02,729 --> 02:55:07,678
“I didn’t mean⁠—” he began,
and paused, his face poisonously

3118
02:55:07,678 --> 02:55:08,409
bloated.

3119
02:55:08,409 --> 02:55:10,679
“Well, I’ll call that sufficient.

3120
02:55:10,679 --> 02:55:12,545
Keep a-standin’ still.

3121
02:55:12,545 --> 02:55:14,582
I ain’ going to trouble yu’ long.

3122
02:55:14,582 --> 02:55:20,551
In admittin’ yourself to be a liar you
have spoke God’s truth for onced.

3123
02:55:20,551 --> 02:55:26,274
Honey Wiggin, you and me and the boys
have hit town too frequent for any of us

3124
02:55:26,274 --> 02:55:29,418
to play Sunday on the
balance of the gang.”

3125
02:55:29,418 --> 02:55:33,957
He stopped and surveyed Public Opinion,
seated around in carefully

3126
02:55:33,957 --> 02:55:35,397
inexpressive attention.

3127
02:55:35,397 --> 02:55:39,357
“We ain’t a Christian outfit a little
bit, and maybe we have most forgotten

3128
02:55:39,357 --> 02:55:40,866
what decency feels like.

3129
02:55:40,866 --> 02:55:43,326
But I reckon we haven’t
forgot what it means.

3130
02:55:43,326 --> -1:59:59,000
You can sit down now, if you want.

3131
-1:59:59,000 --> 00:00:02,000
”

3132
02:55:45,541 --> 02:55:49,240
The liar stood and sneered
experimentally, looking

3133
02:55:49,240 --> 02:55:50,921
at Public Opinion.

3134
02:55:50,921 --> 02:55:55,771
But this changeful deity was no longer
with him, and he heard it variously

3135
02:55:55,771 --> 02:56:00,051
assenting, “That’s so,”
and “She’s a lady,” and

3136
02:56:00,051 --> 02:56:04,055
otherwise excellently moralizing.

3137
02:56:04,055 --> 02:56:05,755
So he held his peace.

3138
02:56:05,755 --> 02:56:09,419
When, however, the Virginian had departed
to the roasting steer,

3139
02:56:09,419 --> 02:56:14,160
and Public Opinion relaxed into that
comfort which we all experience when the

3140
02:56:14,160 --> 02:56:18,363
sermon ends, Trampas sat down amid the
reviving cheerfulness,

3141
02:56:18,363 --> 02:56:20,636
and ventured again to be facetious.

3142
02:56:20,636 --> 02:56:24,374
“Shut your rank mouth,”
said Wiggin to him, amiably.

3143
02:56:24,374 --> 02:56:29,844
“I don’t care whether he knows her or if
he done it on principle.

3144
02:56:29,844 --> 02:56:32,662
I’ll accept the roundin’ up he
gave us⁠—and say!

3145
02:56:32,662 --> 02:56:34,539
You’ll swallo’ your dose, too!

3146
02:56:34,539 --> -1:59:59,000
Us boys’ll stand in with him in this.

3147
-1:59:59,000 --> 00:00:02,000
”

3148
02:56:38,182 --> 02:56:41,665
So Trampas swallowed.

3149
02:56:41,665 --> 02:56:43,987
And what of the Virginian?

3150
02:56:43,987 --> 02:56:47,955
He had championed the feeble,
and spoken honorably in meeting,

3151
02:56:47,955 --> 02:56:51,566
and according to all the constitutions
and bylaws of morality,

3152
02:56:51,566 --> 02:56:54,699
he should have been walking
in virtue’s especial calm.

3153
02:56:54,699 --> 02:56:57,162
But there it was!

3154
02:56:57,162 --> 02:57:04,823
he had spoken; he had given them a peep
through the keyhole at his inner man;

3155
02:57:04,823 --> 02:57:07,884
and as he prowled away from the
assemblage before whom he stood

3156
02:57:07,884 --> 02:57:10,877
convicted of decency,
it was vicious rather than

3157
02:57:10,877 --> 02:57:12,191
virtuous that he felt.

3158
02:57:12,191 --> 02:57:16,889
Other matters also disquieted him⁠—so Lin
McLean was hanging round that

3159
02:57:16,889 --> 02:57:17,837
schoolmarm!

3160
02:57:17,837 --> 02:57:22,374
Yet he joined Ben Swinton in
a seemingly Christian spirit.

3161
02:57:22,374 --> 02:57:26,974
He took some whiskey and praised the size
of the barrel, speaking with

3162
02:57:26,974 --> 02:57:28,311
his host like this:⁠—

3163
02:57:28,311 --> 02:57:32,023
“There cert’nly ain’ goin’ to be trouble
about a second helpin’.”

3164
02:57:32,023 --> 02:57:33,075
“Hope not.

3165
02:57:33,075 --> 02:57:35,555
We’d ought to have more trimmings, though.

3166
02:57:35,555 --> 02:57:37,316
We’re shy on ducks.”

3167
02:57:37,316 --> 02:57:38,796
“Yu’ have the barrel.

3168
02:57:38,796 --> 02:57:41,196
Has Lin McLean seen that?”

3169
02:57:41,196 --> 02:57:42,476
“No.

3170
02:57:42,476 --> 02:57:47,167
We tried for ducks away down as far
as the Laparel outfit.

3171
02:57:47,167 --> 02:57:48,481
A real barbecue⁠—”

3172
02:57:48,481 --> 02:57:51,207
“There’s large thirsts on Bear Creek.

3173
02:57:51,207 --> 02:57:53,461
Lin McLean will pass on ducks.”

3174
02:57:53,461 --> 02:57:56,989
“Lin’s not thirsty this month.”

3175
02:57:56,989 --> -1:59:59,000
“Signed for one month, has he?

3176
-1:59:59,000 --> 00:00:02,000
”

3177
02:58:00,269 --> 02:58:01,267
“Signed!

3178
02:58:01,267 --> 02:58:03,149
He’s spooning our schoolmarm!”

3179
02:58:03,149 --> 02:58:05,637
“They claim she’s a right
sweet-faced girl.”

3180
02:58:05,637 --> 02:58:07,892
“Yes; yes; awful agreeable.

3181
02:58:07,892 --> 02:58:09,927
And next thing you’re
fooled clean through.”

3182
02:58:09,927 --> 02:58:10,739
“Yu’ don’t say!”

3183
02:58:10,739 --> 02:58:14,584
“She keeps a-teaching the darned kids,
and it seems like a good growed-up

3184
02:58:14,584 --> 02:58:17,525
man can’t interest her.”

3185
02:58:17,525 --> 02:58:20,045
“Yu’ don’t say!”

3186
02:58:20,045 --> 02:58:22,685
“There used to be all the ducks you
wanted at the Laparel,

3187
02:58:22,685 --> 02:58:25,985
but their fool cook’s dead stuck on
raising turkeys this year.”

3188
02:58:25,985 --> 02:58:28,605
“That must have been mighty close to a
drowndin’ the schoolmarm

3189
02:58:28,605 --> 02:58:29,685
got at South Fork.”

3190
02:58:29,685 --> 02:58:31,011
“Why, I guess not.

3191
02:58:31,011 --> 02:58:32,514
When?

3192
02:58:32,514 --> 02:58:35,983
She’s never spoken of any such
thing⁠—that I’ve heard.”

3193
02:58:35,983 --> 02:58:39,082
“Mos’ likely the stage-driver
got it wrong, then.”

3194
02:58:39,082 --> 02:58:39,666
“Yes.

3195
02:58:39,666 --> 02:58:41,136
Must have drownded somebody else.

3196
02:58:41,136 --> 02:58:42,233
Here they come!

3197
02:58:42,233 --> 02:58:44,166
That’s her ridin’ the horse.

3198
02:58:44,166 --> 02:58:45,768
There’s the Westfalls.

3199
02:58:45,768 --> 02:58:47,098
Where are you running to?”

3200
02:58:47,098 --> 02:58:47,959
“To fix up.

3201
02:58:47,959 --> 02:58:49,609
Got any soap around hyeh?”

3202
02:58:49,609 --> 02:58:53,609
“Yes,” shouted Swinton,
for the Virginian was now some distance

3203
02:58:53,609 --> 02:58:57,325
away; “towels and everything
in the dugout.”

3204
02:58:57,325 --> 02:59:00,004
And he went to welcome
his first formal guests.

3205
02:59:00,004 --> 02:59:02,581
The Virginian reached his
saddle under a shed.

3206
02:59:02,581 --> 02:59:06,844
“So she’s never mentioned it,”
said he, untying his slicker for

3207
02:59:06,844 --> 02:59:08,506
the trousers and scarf.

3208
02:59:08,506 --> 02:59:10,911
“I didn’t notice Lin anywheres
around her.”

3209
02:59:10,911 --> 02:59:14,892
He was over in the dugout now,
whipping off his overalls;

3210
02:59:14,892 --> 02:59:20,269
and soon he was excellently clean and
ready, except for the tie in his scarf

3211
02:59:20,269 --> 02:59:21,679
and the part in his hair.

3212
02:59:21,679 --> 02:59:24,326
“I’d have knowed her in
Greenland,” he remarked.

3213
02:59:24,326 --> 02:59:28,756
He held the candle up and down at the
looking-glass, and the looking-glass up

3214
02:59:28,756 --> 02:59:29,945
and down at his head.

3215
02:59:29,945 --> 02:59:32,337
“It’s mighty strange why
she ain’t mentioned that.”

3216
02:59:32,337 --> 02:59:35,236
He worried the scarf a fold or two
further, and at length,

3217
02:59:35,236 --> 02:59:39,849
a trifle more than satisfied with his
appearance, he proceeded most serenely

3218
02:59:39,849 --> 02:59:41,805
toward the sound of the tuning fiddles.

3219
02:59:41,805 --> 02:59:46,110
He passed through the storeroom behind
the kitchen, stepping lightly lest he

3220
02:59:46,110 --> 02:59:51,256
should rouse the ten or twelve babies
that lay on the table or beneath it.

3221
02:59:51,256 --> 02:59:55,825
On Bear Creek babies and children always
went with their parents to a dance,

3222
02:59:55,825 --> 02:59:57,472
because nurses were unknown.

3223
02:59:57,472 --> 03:00:02,138
So little Alfred and Christopher lay
there among the wraps,

3224
03:00:02,138 --> 03:00:08,173
parallel and crosswise with little
Taylors, and little Carmodys,

3225
03:00:08,173 --> 03:00:14,096
and Lees, and all the Bear Creek
offspring that was not yet able to skip

3226
03:00:14,096 --> 03:00:22,052
at large and hamper its indulgent
elders in the ballroom.

3227
03:00:22,052 --> 03:00:25,012
“Why, Lin ain’t hyeh yet!”

3228
03:00:25,012 --> 03:00:28,434
said the Virginian, looking
in upon the people.

3229
03:00:28,434 --> 03:00:31,559
There was Miss Wood, standing
up for the quadrille.

3230
03:00:31,559 --> 03:00:34,741
“I didn’t remember her hair was
that pretty,” said he.

3231
03:00:34,741 --> 03:00:36,461
“But ain’t she a little, little girl!”

3232
03:00:36,461 --> 03:00:39,705
Now she was in truth five feet three;
but then he could look away down on the

3233
03:00:39,705 --> 03:00:40,477
top of her head.

3234
03:00:40,477 --> 03:00:42,092
“Salute your honey!”

3235
03:00:42,092 --> 03:00:44,009
called the first fiddler.

3236
03:00:44,009 --> 03:00:48,578
All partners bowed to each other,
and as she turned, Miss Wood saw the

3237
03:00:48,578 --> 03:00:50,673
man in the doorway.

3238
03:00:50,673 --> 03:00:56,301
Again, as it had been at South Fork that
day, his eyes dropped from hers,

3239
03:00:56,301 --> 03:01:00,301
and she divining instantly why he had
come after half a year,

3240
03:01:00,301 --> 03:01:04,385
thought of the handkerchief and of that
scream of hers in the river,

3241
03:01:04,385 --> 03:01:09,013
and became filled with tyranny and
anticipation; for indeed he was

3242
03:01:09,013 --> 03:01:10,293
fine to look upon.

3243
03:01:10,293 --> 03:01:14,242
So she danced away, carefully
unaware of his existence.

3244
03:01:14,242 --> 03:01:16,125
“First lady, centre!”

3245
03:01:16,125 --> 03:01:19,035
said her partner, reminding
her of her turn.

3246
03:01:19,035 --> 03:01:21,594
“Have you forgotten how it
goes since last time?”

3247
03:01:21,594 --> 03:01:24,968
Molly Wood did not forget again,
but quadrilled with the

3248
03:01:24,968 --> 03:01:27,759
most sprightly devotion.

3249
03:01:27,759 --> 03:01:33,632
“I see some new faces
tonight,” said she, presently.

3250
03:01:33,632 --> 03:01:37,832
“Yu’ always do forget our poor
faces,” said her partner.

3251
03:01:37,832 --> 03:01:39,214
“Oh, no!

3252
03:01:39,214 --> 03:01:41,417
There’s a stranger now.

3253
03:01:41,417 --> -1:59:59,000
Who is that black man?

3254
-1:59:59,000 --> 00:00:02,000
”

3255
03:01:43,693 --> 03:01:48,267
“Well⁠—he’s from Virginia,
and he ain’t allowin’ he’s black.”

3256
03:01:48,267 --> 03:01:50,035
“He’s a tenderfoot, I suppose?”

3257
03:01:50,035 --> 03:01:50,873
“Ha, ha, ha!

3258
03:01:50,873 --> 03:01:52,037
That’s rich, too!”

3259
03:01:52,037 --> 03:01:54,635
and so the simple partner explained a
great deal about the

3260
03:01:54,635 --> 03:01:56,177
Virginian to Molly Wood.

3261
03:01:56,177 --> 03:02:00,318
At the end of the set she saw the man by
the door take a step in her direction.

3262
03:02:00,318 --> 03:02:04,881
“Oh,” said she, quickly,
to the partner, “how warm it is!

3263
03:02:04,881 --> 03:02:07,389
I must see how those babies are doing.”

3264
03:02:07,389 --> 03:02:10,399
And she passed the Virginian in
a breeze of unconcern.

3265
03:02:10,399 --> 03:02:13,548
His eyes gravely lingered
where she had gone.

3266
03:02:13,548 --> 03:02:16,348
“She knowed me right away,” said he.

3267
03:02:16,348 --> 03:02:19,500
He looked for a moment,
then leaned against the door.

3268
03:02:19,500 --> 03:02:20,945
“ ’How warm it is!’

3269
03:02:20,945 --> 03:02:21,823
said she.

3270
03:02:21,823 --> 03:02:25,943
Well, it ain’t so screechin’ hot hyeh;
and as for rushin’ after Alfred and

3271
03:02:25,943 --> 03:02:29,903
Christopher, when their natural motheh
is bumpin’ around handy⁠—she

3272
03:02:29,903 --> 03:02:31,497
cert’nly can’t be offended?”

3273
03:02:31,497 --> 03:02:34,215
he broke off, and looked again
where she had gone.

3274
03:02:34,215 --> 03:02:38,446
And then Miss Wood passed him brightly
again, and was dancing

3275
03:02:38,446 --> 03:02:40,988
the schottische almost immediately.

3276
03:02:40,988 --> 03:02:45,750
“Oh, yes, she knows me,”
the swarthy cowpuncher mused.

3277
03:02:45,750 --> 03:02:48,879
“She has to take trouble not to see me.

3278
03:02:48,879 --> 03:02:52,428
And what she’s a-fussin’
at is mighty interestin’.

3279
03:02:52,428 --> 03:02:53,136
Hello!”

3280
03:02:53,136 --> 03:02:54,468
“Hello!”

3281
03:02:54,468 --> 03:02:56,453
returned Lin McLean, sourly.

3282
03:02:56,453 --> 03:02:58,506
He had just looked into the kitchen.

3283
03:02:58,506 --> 03:02:59,867
“Not dancin’?”

3284
03:02:59,867 --> 03:03:01,546
the Southerner inquired.

3285
03:03:01,546 --> 03:03:02,964
“Don’t know how.”

3286
03:03:02,964 --> 03:03:05,656
“Had scyarlet fever and
forgot your past life?”

3287
03:03:05,656 --> 03:03:06,590
Lin grinned.

3288
03:03:06,590 --> 03:03:10,187
“Better persuade the schoolmarm
to learn it.

3289
03:03:10,187 --> -1:59:59,000
She’s goin’ to give me instruction

3290
-1:59:59,000 --> -1:59:59,000
.

3291
-1:59:59,000 --> 00:00:02,000
”

3292
03:03:11,865 --> 03:03:12,656
“Huh!”

3293
03:03:12,656 --> 03:03:15,822
went Mr. McLean, and skulked
out to the barrel.

3294
03:03:15,822 --> 03:03:20,016
“Why, they claimed you
weren’t drinkin’ this month!”

3295
03:03:20,016 --> 03:03:21,646
said his friend, following.

3296
03:03:21,646 --> 03:03:23,057
“Well, I am.

3297
03:03:23,057 --> 03:03:23,798
Here’s luck!”

3298
03:03:23,798 --> 03:03:25,885
The two pledged in tin cups.

3299
03:03:25,885 --> 03:03:30,027
“But I’m not waltzin’ with her,”
blurted Mr. McLean grievously.

3300
03:03:30,027 --> 03:03:32,541
“She called me an exception.”

3301
03:03:32,541 --> 03:03:36,454
“Waltzin’,” repeated the Virginian
quickly, and hearing the

3302
03:03:36,454 --> 03:03:38,229
fiddles he hastened away.

3303
03:03:38,229 --> 03:03:42,644
Few in the Bear Creek Country could
waltz, and with these few it was mostly

3304
03:03:42,644 --> 03:03:48,177
an unsteered and ponderous exhibition;
therefore was the Southerner bent upon

3305
03:03:48,177 --> 03:03:49,805
profiting by his skill.

3306
03:03:49,805 --> 03:03:54,443
He entered the room, and his lady saw him
come where she sat alone for the moment,

3307
03:03:54,443 --> 03:03:56,379
and her thoughts grew a little hurried.

3308
03:03:56,379 --> 03:03:58,085
“Will you try a turn, ma’am?”

3309
03:03:58,085 --> 03:03:59,329
“I beg your pardon?”

3310
03:03:59,329 --> 03:04:04,394
It was a remote, well-schooled eye that
she lifted now upon him.

3311
03:04:04,394 --> 03:04:07,229
“If you like a waltz,
ma’am, will you waltz with me?”

3312
03:04:07,229 --> 03:04:09,553
“You’re from Virginia, I understand?”

3313
03:04:09,553 --> 03:04:14,220
said Molly Wood, regarding him
politely, but not rising.

3314
03:04:14,220 --> 03:04:18,841
One gains authority immensely
by keeping one’s seat.

3315
03:04:18,841 --> 03:04:22,342
All good teachers know this.

3316
03:04:22,342 --> 03:04:24,081
“Yes, ma’am, from Virginia.”

3317
03:04:24,081 --> 03:04:26,426
“I’ve heard that Southerners
have such good manners.”

3318
03:04:26,426 --> 03:04:27,462
“That’s correct.”

3319
03:04:27,462 --> 03:04:30,784
The cowpuncher flushed,
but he spoke in his unvaryingly

3320
03:04:30,784 --> 03:04:31,878
gentle voice.

3321
03:04:31,878 --> 03:04:35,663
“For in New England, you know,”
pursued Miss Molly, noting his scarf and

3322
03:04:35,663 --> 03:04:39,738
clean-shaven chin, and then again
steadily meeting his eye,

3323
03:04:39,738 --> 03:04:44,559
“gentlemen ask to be presented to ladies
before they ask them to waltz.”

3324
03:04:44,559 --> 03:04:49,317
He stood a moment before her,
deeper and deeper scarlet;

3325
03:04:49,317 --> 03:04:54,457
and the more she saw his handsome face,
the keener rose her excitement.

3326
03:04:54,457 --> 03:04:59,173
She waited for him to speak of the river;
for then she was going to be surprised,

3327
03:04:59,173 --> 03:05:03,827
and gradually to remember,
and finally to be very nice to him.

3328
03:05:03,827 --> 03:05:05,176
But he did not wait.

3329
03:05:05,176 --> 03:05:08,660
“I ask your pardon, lady,”
said he, and bowing,

3330
03:05:08,660 --> 03:05:12,930
walked off, leaving her at once afraid
that he might not come back.

3331
03:05:12,930 --> 03:05:16,631
But she had altogether mistaken her man.

3332
03:05:16,631 --> 03:05:21,443
Back he came serenely with Mr. Taylor,
and was duly presented to her.

3333
03:05:21,443 --> 03:05:25,180
Thus were the conventions vindicated.

3334
03:05:25,180 --> 03:05:28,771
It can never be known what the cowpuncher
was going to say next;

3335
03:05:28,771 --> 03:05:32,402
for Uncle Hughey stepped up with a glass
of water which he had left Wood to

3336
03:05:32,402 --> 03:05:37,094
bring, and asking for a turn,
most graciously received it.

3337
03:05:37,094 --> 03:05:41,917
She danced away from a situation where
she began to feel herself getting

3338
03:05:41,917 --> 03:05:42,767
the worst of it.

3339
03:05:42,767 --> 03:05:48,281
One moment the Virginian stared at his
lady as she lightly circulated,

3340
03:05:48,281 --> 03:05:50,035
and then he went out to the barrel.

3341
03:05:50,035 --> 03:05:52,321
Leave him for Uncle Hershey!

3342
03:05:52,321 --> 03:05:57,442
Jealousy is a deep and delicate thing,
and works its spite in many ways.

3343
03:05:57,442 --> 03:06:02,287
The Virginian had been ready to look at
Lin McLean with a hostile eye;

3344
03:06:02,287 --> 03:06:07,098
but finding him now beside the barrel,
he felt a brotherhood between himself

3345
03:06:07,098 --> 03:06:11,096
and Lin, and his hostility had taken a
new and whimsical direction.

3346
03:06:11,096 --> 03:06:11,966
“Here’s how!”

3347
03:06:11,966 --> 03:06:13,458
said he to McLean.

3348
03:06:13,458 --> 03:06:16,529
And they pledged each other
in the tin cups.

3349
03:06:16,529 --> 03:06:19,703
“Been gettin’ them instructions?”

3350
03:06:19,703 --> 03:06:21,758
said Mr. McLean, grinning.

3351
03:06:21,758 --> 03:06:24,729
“I thought I saw yu’ learning your
steps through the window.”

3352
03:06:24,729 --> 03:06:27,304
“Here’s your good health,”
said the Southerner.

3353
03:06:27,304 --> 03:06:31,034
Once more they pledged
each other handsomely.

3354
03:06:31,034 --> 03:06:34,331
“Did she call you an exception,
or anything?”

3355
03:06:34,331 --> 03:06:34,927
said Lin.

3356
03:06:34,927 --> 03:06:38,492
“Well, it would cipher out right
close in that neighborhood.”

3357
03:06:38,492 --> 03:06:39,536
“Here’s how, then!”

3358
03:06:39,536 --> 03:06:42,253
cried the delighted Lin, over his cup.

3359
03:06:42,253 --> 03:06:47,013
“Jest because yu’ happen to come from
Vermont,” continued Mr. McLean,

3360
03:06:47,013 --> 03:06:49,129
“is no cause for extra pride.

3361
03:06:49,129 --> 03:06:49,841
Shoo!

3362
03:06:49,841 --> 03:06:53,425
I was raised in Massachusetts myself,
and big men have been raised there,

3363
03:06:53,425 --> 03:06:58,051
too⁠—Daniel Webster and Israel Putnam:
and a lot of them politicians.”

3364
03:06:58,051 --> 03:07:01,932
“Virginia is a good little old
state,” observed the Southerner.

3365
03:07:01,932 --> 03:07:04,342
“Both of ’em’s a sight ahead of Vermont.

3366
03:07:04,342 --> 03:07:07,549
She told me I was the
first exception she’d struck.”

3367
03:07:07,549 --> 03:07:10,589
“What rule were you provin’
at the time, Lin?”

3368
03:07:10,589 --> 03:07:13,772
“Well yu’ see, I started to kiss her.”

3369
03:07:13,772 --> 03:07:15,151
“Yu’ didn’t!”

3370
03:07:15,151 --> 03:07:16,199
“Shucks!

3371
03:07:16,199 --> 03:07:17,479
I didn’t mean nothin’.”

3372
03:07:17,479 --> 03:07:19,207
“I reckon yu’ stopped mighty sudden?”

3373
03:07:19,207 --> 03:07:23,387
“Why, I’d been ridin’ out with her⁠—
ridin’ to school, ridin’ from school,

3374
03:07:23,387 --> 03:07:26,702
and a-comin’ and a-goin’, and she
chattin’ cheerful and askin’ me a heap

3375
03:07:26,702 --> 03:07:30,868
o’ questions all about myself every day,
and I not lyin’ much neither.

3376
03:07:30,868 --> 03:07:33,062
And so I figured she wouldn’t mind.

3377
03:07:33,062 --> 03:07:34,503
Lots of ’em like it.

3378
03:07:34,503 --> -1:59:59,000
But she didn’t, you bet!

3379
-1:59:59,000 --> 00:00:02,000
”

3380
03:07:36,877 --> 03:07:40,378
“No,” said the Virginian,
deeply proud of his lady

3381
03:07:40,378 --> 03:07:41,468
who had slighted him.

3382
03:07:41,468 --> 03:07:45,277
He had pulled her out of the water once,
and he had been her unrewarded knight

3383
03:07:45,277 --> 03:07:49,629
even today, and he felt his grievance;
but he spoke not of it to Lin;

3384
03:07:49,629 --> 03:07:55,218
for he felt also, in memory,
her arms clinging round him as he

3385
03:07:55,218 --> 03:07:57,417
carried her ashore upon his horse.

3386
03:07:57,417 --> 03:07:59,516
But he muttered, “Plumb ridiculous!”

3387
03:07:59,516 --> 03:08:04,877
as her injustice struck him afresh,
while the outraged McLean told his tale.

3388
03:08:04,877 --> 03:08:09,345
“Trample is what she has done on me
tonight, and without notice.

3389
03:08:09,345 --> 03:08:13,368
We was startin’ to come here;
Taylor and Mrs. were ahead in the buggy,

3390
03:08:13,368 --> 03:08:16,767
and I was holdin’ her horse,
and helpin’ her up in the saddle,

3391
03:08:16,767 --> 03:08:18,914
like I done for days and days.

3392
03:08:18,914 --> 03:08:20,034
Who was there to see us?

3393
03:08:20,034 --> 03:08:24,715
And I figured she’d not mind,
and she calls me an exception!

3394
03:08:24,715 --> 03:08:30,510
Yu’d ought to’ve just heard her about
Western men respectin’ women.

3395
03:08:30,510 --> 03:08:33,070
So that’s the last word we’ve spoke.

